<sect>Introduction

<p>
KMedia is KDE's generic media player. The base system comes with the
ability to play digital audio data (WAV) through KDE's audio server.
You will need the KDE base system (kdelibs + kdebase) for this.
It can be extended by writing mediatool compliant player modules.

